{"id":6349,"date":"2016-07-05T19:25:11","date_gmt":"2016-07-05T19:25:11","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=6349"},"modified":"2019-08-13T16:54:12","modified_gmt":"2019-08-13T16:54:12","slug":"how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/","title":{"rendered":"How to add custom fields to existing work items for VSTS"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"#Intro\">Introduction<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 1\">Step 1: Creating an inherited process<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 2\">Step 2: Setting process security<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 3\">Step 3: Adding New Field<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Step 4\">Step 4: Adding custom fields to existing work item<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#Con\">Conclusion<\/a><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h3 id=\"Intro\">Introduction<\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/en-us\/products\/visual-studio-team-services-vs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Visual Studio Team Services<\/strong><\/a> is designed for all teams and enables them to track work, share codes and ship software. It provides many tools to support managers, architects, testers, project managers, build and documentation teams, and, of course, developers. The service is available in many languages. It\u2019s is free for teams up to 5 users and for additional users is payable. The pricing calculator is available right <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/en-us\/products\/visual-studio-team-services-pricing-vs.aspx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>In this post I\u2019m going to describe one of the latest implemented features from of VSTS process customization, that were completed in first wave. This feature allows users to modify fields of existing work item types.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip<\/span> If you would like to learn more about enhancing Frontend development code quality<\/h3>\n<p class=\"blue\">it includes understanding different types of JavaScript unit testing frameworks like Jasmine, Mocha, Jest, different types of task runner like Grunt and Gulp, different types of linting tools, like JSHint, ESLint, JSLint, CSSLint, different types of code formatter like Prettier and Tidy, how to write your first JavaScript using test with Jasmine standalone version, how to run JavaScript unit tests using Grunt, Command Line and PhantomJS, how to calculate code coverage for JavaScript unit tests using Istanbul, how to run JavaScript unit tests using Visual Studio Test Explorer using chutzpah extension, how to linting JavaScript code using JSHint and how to run that from Command Line using Grunt, finally it shows how to integrate all the quality practices with Visual Studio Team Service Build automation so it can be part of CI\/CD or Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery, &#8211; have a look at the <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/04\/04\/front-end-code-quality-javascript-unit-test-and-linting-automation-with-vsts-build\/\"><strong>this post<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip (<strong><a href=\" https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/06\/08\/getting-started-with-kubernetes-cluster-ci-cd-for-azure-kubernetes-service\/ \"> Kubernetes cluster for beginner <\/a>)<\/strong><\/span> For more information about how to work with Kubernetes cluster and deploy it to <strong>Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) <\/strong>and work with <strong>Azure Container Registry<\/strong>, see <strong><a href=\" https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/06\/08\/getting-started-with-kubernetes-cluster-ci-cd-for-azure-kubernetes-service\/ \">Kubernetes cluster for beginner<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div class=\"ast-oembed-container\" style=\"height: 100%;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Deploy Docker image to Kubernetes Cluster | CI-CD for Azure Kubernetes Service\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/4DUhc0MjdUc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<h3 id=\"Step 1\">Step 1: Creating an inherited process<\/h3>\n<p>This feature enables to extend the work items from any of your processes, such as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.visualstudio.com\/en-us\/docs\/work\/guidance\/choose-process\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Agile, Scrum and CMMI<\/a> and to add your own custom fields to them. Before you can modify the fields on work item types, you will need to create an inherited process.<\/p>\n<p>1. Navigate to your <strong>VSTS admin panel<\/strong> and click on <strong>Processes <\/strong>button.<br \/>\n2. On the selected process click on <strong>dots<\/strong> to open the drop down menu.<br \/>\n3. Click on <strong>Create inherited process option<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/1-1-creating-an-inherited-process-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6350\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6350\" title=\"1-1 Creating an inherited process VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-1-Creating-an-inherited-process-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"1-1 Creating an inherited process VSTS\" width=\"763\" height=\"493\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-1-Creating-an-inherited-process-VSTS.jpg 929w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-1-Creating-an-inherited-process-VSTS-300x194.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-1-Creating-an-inherited-process-VSTS-768x496.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>4. In the <strong>Process name field<\/strong> type the <strong>Name<\/strong> of your process.<br \/>\n5. In the <strong>Process description field<\/strong> type the <strong>Description of your process<\/strong>.<br \/>\n6. Click on <strong>Create Process<\/strong> button.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/1-2-creating-an-inherited-process-from-scrum-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6351\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6351 size-full\" title=\"1-2 Creating an inherited process from Scrum VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-2-Creating-an-inherited-process-from-Scrum-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"1-2 Creating an inherited process from Scrum VSTS\" width=\"583\" height=\"505\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-2-Creating-an-inherited-process-from-Scrum-VSTS.jpg 583w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/1-2-Creating-an-inherited-process-from-Scrum-VSTS-300x260.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 583px) 100vw, 583px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip (<strong><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/05\/31\/docker-for-beginners-step-by-step-tutorial\/\">Docker for beginners<\/a>)<\/strong><\/span> For more information about how to work with <strong>Docker<\/strong> like, pull docker image, run docker image and work with container, see <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/05\/31\/docker-for-beginners-step-by-step-tutorial\/\"> Docker for beginners <\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div class=\"ast-oembed-container\" style=\"height: 100%;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Docker For Beginners Step by Step Tutorial\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/3RJv6yVfaRE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<h3 id=\"Step 2\">Step 2: Setting process security<\/h3>\n<p>You can set for each process security settings for creating, editing and deleting the process. This can be set by team project administrator, who will choose which processes can be inherited from and by whom.<\/p>\n<p>1. You\u2019ll see your created process in the process tab. Click on the <strong>dots<\/strong> to open the drop down menu.<br \/>\n2. From <strong>Drop down Menu<\/strong> choose option <strong>Manage processes security<\/strong>\u00a0to set individual ACL&#8217;s for which users and groups can edit and delete the process.<br \/>\n3. In the new window click on the<strong> User<\/strong> and on the right side of the window you will have the options for <strong>Modification of Permissions<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/2-setting-process-security-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6352\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6352\" title=\"2-Setting process security VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/2-Setting-process-security-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"2-Setting process security VSTS\" width=\"763\" height=\"362\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/2-Setting-process-security-VSTS.jpg 1365w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/2-Setting-process-security-VSTS-300x142.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/2-Setting-process-security-VSTS-768x364.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/2-Setting-process-security-VSTS-1024x485.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Step 3\">Step 3: Adding New Field<\/h3>\n<p>1. Navigate back to the <strong>Processes tab<\/strong> in settings area and click on <strong>Work Item Types<\/strong>.<br \/>\n2. Click on <strong>Fields<\/strong> under <strong>Task section<\/strong>, to add new field to a task.<br \/>\n3. Click on <strong>New Field<\/strong> button.<br \/>\n4. In new window define the <strong>New Fields parameters<\/strong>. In this example, I will add a field for <strong>&lt;Deadline Date&gt;<\/strong> of a task.<br \/>\n5. Click on <strong>Add Field<\/strong> button.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/3-adding-new-fields-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6353\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6353\" title=\"3-Adding New Fields VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/3-Adding-New-Fields-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"3-Adding New Fields VSTS\" width=\"763\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/3-Adding-New-Fields-VSTS.jpg 1363w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/3-Adding-New-Fields-VSTS-300x138.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/3-Adding-New-Fields-VSTS-768x352.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/3-Adding-New-Fields-VSTS-1024x470.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">Tip (<a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/05\/31\/mastering-git-from-beginner-to-advanced-step-by-step-with-graphical-animation-commands\/\"><strong>Mastering Git with animation<\/strong>) <\/a><\/span> For more information about how to work with <strong>Git<\/strong> with animation. All commands will be represented in graphical animation. E.g. git branch, git merge, git rebase, git cherry-pick and many others, see <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2019\/05\/31\/mastering-git-from-beginner-to-advanced-step-by-step-with-graphical-animation-commands\/\"> Mastering Git with animation<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div class=\"ast-oembed-container\" style=\"height: 100%;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Mastering Git From Beginner to Advanced Step by Step With Graphical Animation Commands\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/ZgCCnv9LxzA?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span>If you would like to learn more about how to work with SSRS PowerShell so we can remap SSRS or SQL Sever Reporting Server Database to an existing DB, we will see also how to restore SSRS encryption key &#8211; have a look at this post &#8211; have a look at the <a href=\" https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/04\/23\/working-with-ssrs-sql-server-reporting-server-powershell\/\"><strong>this post<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Step 4\">Step 4: Adding custom fields to existing work item<\/h3>\n<p>In this step I\u2019m going to show you, how we will add the field that was created in previous steps to a task.<\/p>\n<p>1. Navigate back to your <strong>Board<\/strong> and open a task. In upper right corner click on <strong>dots<\/strong>, to open the drop down menu.<br \/>\n2. From drop down menu chose option <strong>Customize<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/4-1-adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6354\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6354\" title=\"4-1 Adding custom fields to existing work item in VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-1-Adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"4-1 Adding custom fields to existing work item in VSTS\" width=\"763\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-1-Adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS.jpg 1371w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-1-Adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-300x133.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-1-Adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-768x341.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-1-Adding-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-1024x455.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>3. In new window in the upper left corner choose the process that was created in previous steps <strong>&lt;My Scrum&gt;<\/strong>.<br \/>\n4. Navigate to <strong>Task<\/strong> and click on it.<br \/>\n5. From the menu click on <strong>Fields<\/strong>.<br \/>\n6. In the right window scroll down to previous created <strong>Field<\/strong>, which has in this case the name <strong>&lt;Deadline Date&gt;<\/strong>. Click on the dots to open the drop down menu.<br \/>\n7. From drop down menu click on <strong>Edit<\/strong> to define parameters of new field.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/4-2-editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6355\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6355\" title=\"4-2 Editing custom fields to existing work item in VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-2-Editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"4-2 Editing custom fields to existing work item in VSTS\" width=\"763\" height=\"359\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-2-Editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS.jpg 1369w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-2-Editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-300x141.jpg 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-2-Editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-768x362.jpg 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-2-Editing-custom-fields-to-existing-work-item-in-VSTS-1024x482.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>8. In the new window you will have the chance to define <strong>Definition<\/strong>, <strong>Options<\/strong> and <strong>Layout<\/strong>. The most important is <strong>Layout<\/strong>, so click on that field.<br \/>\n9. On the right side you will have the chance to define the exact layout of the new filed. You can correct the <strong>Label Name<\/strong> and chose the <strong>Layout<\/strong> of new <strong>Field<\/strong> in task.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/4-3-editing-custom-field-layout-in-vsts\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-6356\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-6356 size-full\" title=\"4-3 Editing custom field layout in VSTS\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-3-Editing-custom-field-layout-in-VSTS.jpg\" alt=\"4-3 Editing custom field layout in VSTS\" width=\"653\" height=\"647\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-3-Editing-custom-field-layout-in-VSTS.jpg 653w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-3-Editing-custom-field-layout-in-VSTS-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/07\/4-3-Editing-custom-field-layout-in-VSTS-300x297.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 653px) 100vw, 653px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"blue\"><span class=\"ion-tip\">Tip<\/span> If you would like to learn more about how to change the credential of IIS Application Pool using PowerShell, we will also use PowerShell to restart the Application Pool &#8211; have a look at this post &#8211; have a look at the <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/04\/23\/working-with-iis-powershell\/\"><strong>this post<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p class=\"green\"><span class=\"ion-info\">More Info<\/span> If you would like to learn more about how to use PowerShell to change some values for Microsoft Dynamics 365 &#8211; have a look at this post &#8211; have a look at the <a href=\" https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2018\/04\/23\/working-with-microsoft-dynamics-365-powershell\/ \"><strong>this post<\/strong><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3 id=\"Con\">Conclusion<\/h3>\n<p>These new features are really amazing and they were implemented to improve user experience and design. In next month\u2019s we can expect even more great work from<strong> VSTS team<\/strong> which should allow users to create custom work item types that can be used on the backlog, to share custom fields between different processes and improvements for custom states. I\u2019m sure that we can expect also some other great features.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction Step 1: Creating an inherited process Step 2: Setting &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2016\/07\/05\/how-to-add-custom-fields-to-existing-work-items\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">How to add custom fields to existing work items for VSTS<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[15,837,17,23,44,834],"tags":[60,70,205,481,8